From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] p2: co-locate Unicode deallocation with type init

HIL telemetry reached the 113-entry static-type loop but spent most of its
time alternating between type-initialization overlay group 7 and Unicode
overlay group 0xc6.  Stub 0x448 is unicode_dealloc(): descriptor creation
interns many names that already exist, and intern_common() decrefs each
discarded temporary through the indirect tp_dealloc slot.  The indirect
type-slot edge was not visible in the direct successful-path closure.

Move unicode_dealloc() into group 7 so this common decref stays in the
already-loaded image.  Keep _PyUnicode_ExactDealloc() with its sole callee;
otherwise specialized bytecode deallocation would acquire a new nested
0xc6-to-7 transition.  The two linked bodies total 516 bytes, while the
measured group-7 image has 19,868 bytes of slot headroom.  Attributes are
P2-only through _Py_P2_INIT_OVERLAY and do not change other targets.
---
 Include/internal/pycore_unicodeobject.h | 3 ++-
 Objects/unicodeobject.c                 | 4 ++--
 2 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Include/internal/pycore_unicodeobject.h b/Include/internal/pycore_unicodeobject.h
--- a/Include/internal/pycore_unicodeobject.h
+++ b/Include/internal/pycore_unicodeobject.h
@@ -32,7 +32,8 @@ PyAPI_FUNC(int) _PyUnicode_CheckConsistency(
     PyObject *op,
     int check_content);
 
-PyAPI_FUNC(void) _PyUnicode_ExactDealloc(PyObject *op);
+PyAPI_FUNC(void) _PyUnicode_ExactDealloc(PyObject *op)
+    _Py_P2_INIT_OVERLAY;
 extern Py_ssize_t _PyUnicode_InternedSize(void);
 extern Py_ssize_t _PyUnicode_InternedSize_Immortal(void);
 
diff --git a/Objects/unicodeobject.c b/Objects/unicodeobject.c
--- a/Objects/unicodeobject.c
+++ b/Objects/unicodeobject.c
@@ -1692,7 +1692,7 @@ find_maxchar_surrogates(const wchar_t *begin, const wchar_t *end,
     return 0;
 }
 
-static void
+_Py_P2_INIT_OVERLAY static void
 unicode_dealloc(PyObject *unicode)
 {
 #ifdef Py_DEBUG
@@ -14942,7 +14942,7 @@ onError:
     return NULL;
 }
 
-void
+_Py_P2_INIT_OVERLAY void
 _PyUnicode_ExactDealloc(PyObject *op)
 {
     assert(PyUnicode_CheckExact(op));
-- 
